From b373ca0936662029cd0117c2986e466fffcab488 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pedro <leme.baseapr@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 20:54:50 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(s58): admin impersonation + config versioning & rollback
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Feature A1 — Admin impersonation (module `impersonation`):
- Schema: ImpersonationSession (tokenHash @unique, actor/target FKs, expiresAt,
  isActive, reason, ipAddress?, userAgent?). Migration adds AuditAction enum
  values IMPERSONATE_START + IMPERSONATE_END.
- Token security: imp_${randomBytes(24).toString('base64url')} = 192 bits
  entropy. Plaintext returned ONCE; SHA-256 hash persisted.
- RBAC matrix (assertCanImpersonate): OWNER → any non-OWNER, ADMIN →
  MANAGER/VENDOR only. Self-impersonation + inactive target rejected.
  Duration clamp [5, 240] min, default 30.
- Service: start/end/resolveByToken (lazy-expire with audit trail)/listActive/
  findById/expireStale. ForbiddenException in end() if actor mismatch.
- Endpoints: POST /impersonation/start, DELETE /impersonation/:id,
  GET /impersonation/sessions, GET /impersonation/sessions/:id —
  @Roles(OWNER, ADMIN) + TenantGuard + RolesGuard.
- Frontend: /dashboard/admin/impersonate with RBAC-gated target picker,
  duration/reason inputs, one-shot token banner, active sessions table.

Feature A2 — Config versioning & rollback (module `config-snapshots`):
- Schema: ConfigSnapshot (companyId, resource enum, resourceId?, snapshotData
  Json, label?, actorId? SET NULL). New enum ConfigResource (5 values).
  AuditAction ROLLBACK.
- 3-phase rollback: (1) pre-capture live state OUTSIDE transaction (preserves
  tx budget); (2) INSIDE tx: create pre-rollback snapshot labeled
  "pre-rollback of <id>" + applyRollback per resource + auditLog ROLLBACK —
  fully atomic + reversible via preRollbackSnapshotId.
- Defensive findFirst guards in applyRollback: FEATURE_FLAG/SLA_POLICY/
  ASSIGNMENT_RULE throw "no longer exists" rather than resurrecting
  soft-deleted config. NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES replace semantics via
  deleteMany + for-loop create per-row with skip-on-fail.
- @OnEvent('config.changed') ingestion from 5 consumer services (companies,
  feature-flags, sla-policies, assignment-rules, notification-preferences) —
  fire-and-forget non-blocking.
- plainOf<T>(row) strips Prisma Date/Decimal prototypes for byte-stable diff
  comparisons.
- Endpoints: GET / (OWNER/ADMIN/MANAGER), GET /:id, POST /, GET /:id/diff,
  POST /:id/rollback (OWNER/ADMIN).
- Frontend: /dashboard/settings/snapshots with list + diff viewer + rollback
  button with confirm.

Tests: impersonation.service.spec.ts + config-snapshots.service.spec.ts.
Updated spec files for 5 consumer services with EventEmitter2 mock.

Resilience: zero circular deps (modules import only PrismaModule +
EventEmitter2), one-shot token issuance, lazy-expire in resolveByToken,
3-phase rollback preserves tx budget, fire-and-forget @OnEvent protects hot
path of 5 consumer services, plainOf normalizes for diff stability.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
