+### 2.5.17 Sessão 58 — 21/04/2026
+
+**Objetivo:** 2 features enterprise (opção A — admin/compliance) — Admin impersonation com RBAC-gated target picker + SHA-256 token one-shot issuance + sessões 5-240min com audit trail bilateral + Config versioning com snapshots append-only + diff viewer + atomic `$transaction` rollback que cria pre-rollback snapshot primeiro (reversível) + @OnEvent auto-ingest.
+
+**Feature A1 — Admin impersonation (módulo novo `impersonation`):**
+- Schema: modelo `ImpersonationSession` (id, companyId, actorUserId, targetUserId, reason Text, tokenHash String @unique, ipAddress?, userAgent?, isActive Bool default true, expiresAt, endedAt?, endedReason?, createdAt, updatedAt). Índices `[companyId, isActive]`, `[actorUserId, createdAt desc]`, `[targetUserId, createdAt desc]`. CASCADE em Company, RESTRICT em User (actor + target). `AuditAction` enum expandido (+IMPERSONATE_START, +IMPERSONATE_END → total 13 valores). Migration `20260428010000_add_impersonation_and_config_snapshots` (agrupada com A2).
+- `ImpersonationService`:
+  1. **`start(companyId, actor, dto, clientInfo?)`** — valida `companyId` não vazio, rejeita self-impersonation (`actor.id === dto.targetUserId` → BadRequest), findFirst target tenant-scoped (NotFoundException cross-tenant), rejeita inactive target (BadRequest), `assertCanImpersonate(actor.role, target.role)` aplica matrix RBAC. Clamp `duration ∈ [MIN_DURATION_MIN=5, MAX_DURATION_MIN=240]` default `DEFAULT_DURATION_MIN=30` (BadRequest fora do range). Gera token `imp_${randomBytes(24).toString('base64url')}` = 192 bits entropia. DB persiste apenas `tokenHash = createHash('sha256').update(token).digest('hex')`. Retorna `StartImpersonationResult {sessionId, token (plaintext, ÚNICA vez), targetUserId, targetUserName, targetUserEmail, expiresAt}`. Audit IMPERSONATE_START resource literal `'IMPERSONATION_SESSION'` fire-and-forget.
+  2. **`end(companyId, actorUserId, sessionId, reason?)`** — findFirst tenant-scoped (NotFoundException), idempotent no-op se `!isActive`, **ForbiddenException** se `session.actorUserId !== actorUserId` (apenas o iniciador pode encerrar), update `{isActive: false, endedAt: now, endedReason: reason ?? 'actor_exit'}`. Audit IMPERSONATE_END.
+  3. **`resolveByToken(token)`** — reject `token.length < 16`. `findUnique({tokenHash})` (O(1) via @unique index). Null/`!isActive` → null. **Lazy-expire**: se `expiresAt.getTime() <= Date.now()` → `update({isActive: false, endedAt: now, endedReason: 'expired'})` + audit IMPERSONATE_END reason='expired' + retorna null (evita uso de token vencido mesmo antes do cron rodar). Sucesso → retorna `ImpersonationContext {sessionId, actorUserId, targetUserId, expiresAt, reason}`.
+  4. **`listActive(companyId, actorUserId?)`** — findMany `{companyId, isActive: true, expiresAt: {gt: now}}` + optional `actorUserId` filter, orderBy `createdAt desc`, take 100.
+  5. **`findById(companyId, id)`** — NotFoundException cross-tenant, include `actor + target` com `{id, name, email}` select.
+  6. **`expireStale()` cron helper** — `updateMany({where: {isActive: true, expiresAt: {lte: now}}, data: {isActive: false, endedAt: now, endedReason: 'expired'}})` bulk cleanup. Retorna count (observabilidade via logger.debug quando > 0). Pode ser wrapped em `@Cron` por scheduler externo sem circular dep.
+  7. **`assertCanImpersonate(actorRole, targetRole)` RBAC matrix**: OWNER → any non-OWNER (Forbidden se OWNER→OWNER); ADMIN → MANAGER | VENDOR (Forbidden caso contrário); demais roles → Forbidden ("only OWNER or ADMIN may impersonate"). Matrix idêntica no front (canImpersonate helper em `page.tsx`) para esconder candidatos inválidos antes do submit — backend é source of truth.
+  8. `hashToken(token)` helper privado. `audit()` fire-and-forget try/catch com warn log (hot path protegido).
+- Endpoints (`@Controller('impersonation')` + `@UseGuards(TenantGuard, RolesGuard)` class-level + `@Roles(UserRole.OWNER, UserRole.ADMIN)`):
+  - `POST /impersonation/start` body `StartImpersonationDto {targetUserId, reason, durationMinutes?}` — extrai `ipAddress` de `x-forwarded-for` (split comma, first trimmed) → fallback `req.ip ?? req.socket?.remoteAddress`, truncate `userAgent` a 500 chars.
+  - `DELETE /impersonation/:id` body/query `reason?` — encerra sessão (ForbiddenException se não-actor).
+  - `GET /impersonation/sessions?actorUserId?` — lista ativas.
+  - `GET /impersonation/sessions/:id` — detail com actor/target hydrate.
+  - Todos os `:id` params com `ParseUUIDPipe`.
+- DTO: `StartImpersonationDto {targetUserId: uuid, reason: string @Length(MIN_REASON=10, MAX_REASON=500), durationMinutes?: @IsInt @Min(5) @Max(240)?}`.
+- Frontend: `/dashboard/admin/impersonate` com 3 cards: (1) `tokenBanner` amber quando `issued` (ÚNICA vez — mostra token base64url + copy button + expiresAt formatado via `Intl.DateTimeFormat(locale, {dateStyle: 'short', timeStyle: 'short'})` + dismiss X), (2) `newSession` com select de targets filtrados por `canImpersonate(actorRole, u.role) && u.id !== self.id` + textarea reason (maxLength 500, char counter, minLength hint via `reasonHint` i18n `{{min}}`) + input number duration (step 5, `durationHint` com `{{min}} {{max}}`), (3) `activeSessions` list com `refetchInterval: 30_000` + status expired badge quando `expires < now` + botão `end` per-row. `canStartImpersonation = actorRole === 'OWNER' || 'ADMIN'` guarda toda a UI; VENDOR/MANAGER veem card `notAllowed` amber. `impersonationService` em `/services` com `start/end/listActive`. Link em `/dashboard/settings` com icon `Eye`.
+- i18n: ~25 chaves (`impersonation.*` — title/subtitle/notAllowed/target/pickTarget/noEligible/reason/reasonPh/reasonHint (com `{{min}}`)/durationMinutes/durationHint (com `{{min}} {{max}}`)/start/end/newSession/expiresAt/startedAt/activeSessions/empty + `tokenBanner.{title, showOnce}` + `toast.{startOk, startErr, endOk, endErr, pickTarget, reasonShort, reasonLong, durationRange, copyErr}`) em pt-BR + en.
+
+**Feature A2 — Config versioning & rollback (módulo novo `config-snapshots`):**
+- Schema: modelo `ConfigSnapshot` (id, companyId, actorId? FK SET NULL, resource `ConfigResource`, resourceId String?, label String?, snapshotData Json, createdAt). Índices `[companyId, resource, createdAt desc]`, `[companyId, createdAt desc]`, `[resource, resourceId]`. CASCADE em Company. Enum novo `ConfigResource` (5 valores: COMPANY_SETTINGS, FEATURE_FLAG, SLA_POLICY, ASSIGNMENT_RULE, NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES). `AuditAction` enum +ROLLBACK (agora 13 total). Migration agrupada com A1.
+- `ConfigSnapshotsService`:
+  1. **`list(companyId, {resource?, resourceId?, limit?})`** — clamp limit `[1..LIST_MAX_LIMIT=200]` default `LIST_DEFAULT_LIMIT=50`, orderBy `createdAt desc`.
+  2. **`findById(companyId, id)`** — NotFoundException cross-tenant.
+  3. **`create(companyId, actorId, dto)`** — `captureLiveState(companyId, resource, resourceId)` lê o estado atual do DB + `snapshotData.create`. Label opcional para identificação humana. Audit CREATE resource literal `'CONFIG_SNAPSHOT'` fire-and-forget.
+  4. **`diff(companyId, id)`** — load snapshot tenant-scoped + `captureLiveState` com mesmos `resource + resourceId` + compara via `JSON.stringify(plainOf(snap.snapshotData)) !== JSON.stringify(plainOf(current))`. Retorna `{snapshotId, resource, resourceId, createdAt, snapshotData, currentData, changed}`.
+  5. **`rollback(companyId, actorId, id)` — 3 fases**:
+     - **Fase 1** (fora do `$transaction`): `captureLiveState(companyId, resource, resourceId)` captura estado corrente **antes** da tx para preservar budget de timeout (I/O de read não polui a tx).
+     - **Fase 2** (dentro de `$transaction`): (a) `prisma.configSnapshot.create` com label `"pre-rollback of ${snap.id}"` persistindo `preRollbackSnapshot` = estado corrente; (b) `applyRollback(tx, companyId, snap)` dispatch por resource; (c) `auditLog.create` com `action: AuditAction.ROLLBACK, resource: 'CONFIG_SNAPSHOT', newValues: {rolledBackTo: snap.id, preRollbackSnapshotId, targetResource, targetResourceId}`.
+     - **Fase 3**: retorna `{success: true, preRollbackSnapshotId}` — cliente pode rollback-of-rollback usando o `preRollbackSnapshotId` (totalmente reversível).
+  6. **`applyRollback(tx, companyId, snap)`** dispatch por `ConfigResource`:
+     - `COMPANY_SETTINGS` → `tx.company.update({where: {id: companyId}, data: {settings: snap.snapshotData}})`.
+     - `FEATURE_FLAG` → **defensive guard**: `tx.featureFlag.findFirst({id: resourceId, companyId})` antes do update — se deletado pós-snapshot, throw `"feature flag no longer exists"` (não re-cria soft-deleted config via rollback). Update com fields do snapshot (name, enabled, rolloutPercentage, userAllowlist, description).
+     - `SLA_POLICY` → mesma guard `findFirst` + update (responseMins, resolutionMins, isActive).
+     - `ASSIGNMENT_RULE` → mesma guard + update (name, priority, strategy, conditions, targetUserIds, isActive).
+     - `NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES` → **replace semantics** por userId (resourceId): `tx.notificationPreference.deleteMany({where: {userId: snap.resourceId, companyId}})` + for-loop `tx.notificationPreference.create` por row do snapshot, **cada create envolto em try/catch skip-on-fail** (handles rows que apontam para user/type/channel inválido após snapshot — mais seguro que per-row upsert).
+  7. **`captureLiveState(companyId, resource, resourceId)`** — 5-branch switch. Cada branch faz `findFirst/findMany` tenant-scoped + retorna `plainOf(row)` (JSON round-trip para byte-stable diff, descarta prototypes Prisma Date/Decimal).
+  8. **`plainOf<T>(row): T`** helper — `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(row))`. Drop prototypes garante `JSON.stringify(a) === JSON.stringify(b)` quando estruturalmente iguais (essencial para diff.changed determinístico).
+  9. **`@OnEvent(CONFIG_CHANGED_EVENT='config.changed')` `handleConfigChanged(payload)`** — fire-and-forget consumer. try/catch warn log. Payload `{companyId, actorId?, resource, resourceId?, label?}`. Chama `create()` internamente — snapshots são criados **automaticamente** sem intervenção manual a cada mutação relevante.
+- **Event producers**: 5 services relevantes emitem `eventEmitter.emit('config.changed', {companyId, actorId, resource, resourceId?, label?})` após mutações (create/update/remove) — try/catch envolve cada emit para nunca quebrar o caller:
+  - `companies.service.ts` → `resource: COMPANY_SETTINGS` em update de settings.
+  - `feature-flags.service.ts` → `resource: FEATURE_FLAG, resourceId: flag.id`.
+  - `sla-policies.service.ts` → `resource: SLA_POLICY, resourceId: policy.id`.
+  - `assignment-rules.service.ts` → `resource: ASSIGNMENT_RULE, resourceId: rule.id`.
+  - `notification-preferences.service.ts` → `resource: NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES, resourceId: userId` (per-user scope, batch changes em um único snapshot via debounce opcional futuro).
+- Endpoints (`@Controller('config-snapshots')` + `@UseGuards(TenantGuard, RolesGuard)` class-level):
+  - `GET /config-snapshots?resource=&resourceId=&limit=` (OWNER/ADMIN/MANAGER list).
+  - `GET /config-snapshots/:id` (OWNER/ADMIN/MANAGER).
+  - `POST /config-snapshots` body `CreateSnapshotDto {resource, resourceId?, label?}` (OWNER/ADMIN manual capture).
+  - `GET /config-snapshots/:id/diff` (OWNER/ADMIN/MANAGER).
+  - `POST /config-snapshots/:id/rollback` (OWNER/ADMIN) — retorna `{success, preRollbackSnapshotId}`.
+  - Todos os `:id` params com `ParseUUIDPipe`.
+- Frontend: `/dashboard/settings/snapshots` com filtros (resource select + resourceId input + limit 1-200), list table com `createdAt` + `resource` badge + `resourceId` code + `label` + actor name, expand row abre diff viewer side-by-side (`snapshotData` vs `currentData`) + changed badge verde/amber, botão `Rollback` com confirm dialog exibindo preview do snapshot a ser aplicado + label `"pre-rollback será criado automaticamente"`. Polling `refetchInterval: 60_000`. `configSnapshotsService` em `/services` com `list/findById/create/diff/rollback`. Link em `/dashboard/settings` com icon `History`.
+- i18n: ~25 chaves (`snapshots.*` — title/subtitle/new/create/resource/resourceId/label/capture/filter/empty/diff.{noChange, changed, current, captured}/rollback.{action, confirm, success, warning}/col.* + `snapshots.resources.{COMPANY_SETTINGS,FEATURE_FLAG,SLA_POLICY,ASSIGNMENT_RULE,NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES}` labels + `toast.*`) em pt-BR + en. Resource labels pt-BR: `COMPANY_SETTINGS: "Configurações da empresa"`, `FEATURE_FLAG: "Feature flag"`, `SLA_POLICY: "Política de SLA"`, `ASSIGNMENT_RULE: "Regra de atribuição"`, `NOTIFICATION_PREFERENCES: "Preferências de notificação"`.
+
+**Integração com features prévias:**
+- `ImpersonationModule` importa apenas `PrismaModule` — zero circular deps. Pode futuramente expor `resolveByToken` a um AuthGuard custom (`X-Impersonation-Token` header) para substituir contexto de auth em requests específicos (feature futura, não wired no S58).
+- `ConfigSnapshotsModule` importa `PrismaModule` + injeta `EventEmitter2` (S46). Reusa infra existente.
+- `EventEmitterModule.forRoot()` já global (S46), `@OnEvent('config.changed')` registra listener automaticamente via DI.
+- 5 consumer services (`companies`, `feature-flags`, `sla-policies`, `assignment-rules`, `notification-preferences`) adicionam `EventEmitter2` ao construtor + emit em mutações. Nenhum deles importa `ConfigSnapshotsModule` — apenas emitem via bus (desacoplamento total).
+- `AuditAction` enum expandido com 3 valores (`IMPERSONATE_START`, `IMPERSONATE_END`, `ROLLBACK`) — total 13. Backward-compat: enums Prisma são additive (não quebram queries existentes).
+
+**Testes:**
